WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:12.000
We have discussed the options for the development of a home network, the strategy of production.

00:12.000 --> 00:18.000
And now, within the framework of technology development, we will consider how to choose our intermediaries,

00:18.000 --> 00:24.000
since we have seen that one of the big mistakes is the wrong choice of intermediaries,

00:24.000 --> 00:27.000
because the product is not competent, not clear, without calculations.

00:27.000 --> 00:33.000
Let's take a look. The slide shows the factors that affect the choice of intermediaries,

00:33.000 --> 00:36.000
and we will now consider them.

00:36.000 --> 00:41.000
The first characteristic of a product that affects the choice of intermediaries is the shelf life of the product.

00:41.000 --> 00:46.000
Why does it affect? In this case, you need to choose intermediaries that have warehouses,

00:46.000 --> 00:51.000
that have refrigeration equipment, an automation system, a logistics system,

00:51.000 --> 00:56.000
so that you can deliver the product on time. This limits your choice of intermediaries.

00:56.000 --> 00:58.000
Not all companies have such resources.

00:58.000 --> 01:02.000
The next factor is the technological and technical complexity of the product.

01:02.000 --> 01:07.000
As I said, for technically complex products, you need companies that are specialists in this.

01:07.000 --> 01:12.000
If your product is not presented by specialists, for example, you go to the medical equipment market

01:12.000 --> 01:19.000
and work with a company that has no idea of medical terms, specializations at all.

01:20.000 --> 01:26.000
It will be very difficult for them to communicate with doctors and explain to them what is the best product.

01:26.000 --> 01:30.000
The next point is an innovative product. We have already talked about it.

01:30.000 --> 01:34.000
I drew your attention to the fact that it is the most difficult to sell a new product,

01:34.000 --> 01:36.000
and not every company will do it.

01:36.000 --> 01:43.000
Therefore, choose a limited number of intermediaries who can present your product competently,

01:43.000 --> 01:45.000
and most importantly, agree to do it.

01:45.000 --> 01:47.000
A heavy and oversized product.

01:47.000 --> 01:49.000
This is where the logistics system comes in.

01:49.000 --> 01:50.000
This is the first point.

01:50.000 --> 01:52.000
And the second point is the availability of storage spaces.

01:52.000 --> 01:57.000
Not every company has a resource for storing and transporting complex and oversized products.

01:57.000 --> 02:05.000
Therefore, one of the limitations will be the weight and dimensions of the product.

02:05.000 --> 02:07.000
A standardized product.

02:07.000 --> 02:11.000
It is easiest to sell and choose intermediaries for this.

02:11.000 --> 02:19.000
These are mostly dealers who sell products to competing companies, including yours.

02:19.000 --> 02:23.000
The sales system will be the cheapest here.

02:23.000 --> 02:26.000
Because you don't need to look for specialized companies,

02:26.000 --> 02:30.000
you just need to go through the market and see who does it better.

02:30.000 --> 02:32.000
A wide range of products.

02:32.000 --> 02:33.000
A line.

02:33.000 --> 02:37.000
If you have a certain line developed in a trading brand,

02:38.000 --> 02:42.000
and it is wide enough, not every company will agree to take the whole line.

02:42.000 --> 02:44.000
What do companies usually say?

02:44.000 --> 02:48.000
We don't need a large range, because not all products in this line are sold,

02:48.000 --> 02:51.000
and not all are of interest to the client.

02:51.000 --> 02:55.000
Yes, it may be so, but there is a certain dependence.

02:55.000 --> 02:59.000
If you represent not a line, but certain positions,

02:59.000 --> 03:04.000
one or two buyers have an opinion that there is no choice,

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
and they do not make a choice.

03:06.000 --> 03:10.000
Therefore, there must be a certain range of products.

03:10.000 --> 03:12.000
And the price of a single product.

03:12.000 --> 03:18.000
Of course, this is important, because some companies specialize in the sale of exclusive products.

03:18.000 --> 03:23.000
Someone specializes in the sale of low-priced products,

03:23.000 --> 03:26.000
and someone specializes in the sale of medium-priced products.

03:26.000 --> 03:29.000
I want to say that this is a very large specificity.

03:29.000 --> 03:35.000
A company that is focused on the low-priced goods market

03:35.000 --> 03:38.000
cannot supply exclusive products.

03:38.000 --> 03:41.000
It will not even be taken seriously on the market.

03:41.000 --> 03:46.000
Therefore, the price very well determines the category and qualification of the intermediary

03:46.000 --> 03:49.000
that will work with your product.

03:49.000 --> 03:53.000
The next factor that we will consider is the characteristics of the company itself.

03:53.000 --> 03:57.000
The company that will work with your product.

03:57.000 --> 03:58.000
What is the first factor?

03:58.000 --> 04:00.000
The first is the company's goals.

04:00.000 --> 04:02.000
What is the goal?

04:02.000 --> 04:04.000
It can be the development of your range,

04:04.000 --> 04:08.000
or becoming a logistics operator,

04:08.000 --> 04:11.000
or working with several brands.

04:11.000 --> 04:19.000
The task here is to understand whether your goals and the goals of this company coincide or not.

04:19.000 --> 04:23.000
And here, of course, they must be in the same direction,

04:23.000 --> 04:27.000
otherwise your product will be completely out of place in this company.

04:27.000 --> 04:30.000
The financial capabilities of the company are a very important factor.

04:30.000 --> 04:34.000
Because if the financial capabilities are limited, what will happen?

04:34.000 --> 04:38.000
You will have a permanent debitory debt,

04:38.000 --> 04:41.000
because the product cannot be paid.

04:41.000 --> 04:44.000
Or there will be a limitation on promotion,

04:44.000 --> 04:47.000
because there is no money for promotion of the product.

04:47.000 --> 04:53.000
Or there will be a delay in payment of transport services,

04:53.000 --> 04:55.000
and the goods cannot be delivered.

04:55.000 --> 04:59.000
Or there will be an illiterate logistics warehouse,

04:59.000 --> 05:02.000
and a lot of problems that are behind it.

05:02.000 --> 05:06.000
Therefore, the financial stability of the company is a very important factor,

05:06.000 --> 05:09.000
and this, fortunately, can be checked.

05:09.000 --> 05:14.000
The next factor that must be taken into account is the assortment.

05:14.000 --> 05:18.000
The assortment is based on your product category.

05:18.000 --> 05:21.000
If the company already has a full assortment,

05:22.000 --> 05:26.000
then it is not a fact that your product will occupy a key position in this company.

05:26.000 --> 05:33.000
You should always look at how many manufacturers the intermediary company works with.

05:33.000 --> 05:36.000
It is believed that there should be no more than 10-15 manufacturers,

05:36.000 --> 05:41.000
and if there are 40, 50 or 80 of them, then it is not worth working with this company.

05:41.000 --> 05:45.000
Your product will be lost in a huge assortment of this company

05:45.000 --> 05:48.000
and will never occupy a leading position.

05:48.000 --> 05:52.000
Unless, of course, it is some kind of know-how on the market.

05:52.000 --> 05:58.000
The next point is the need for control and the possibility of control.

05:58.000 --> 06:02.000
Because not every company provides information about itself.

06:02.000 --> 06:04.000
But here is the question.

06:04.000 --> 06:08.000
If it does not provide information about itself, then should you work with it?

06:08.000 --> 06:12.000
If the company has something to hide, is it good for you?

06:12.000 --> 06:15.000
The next factors that we will consider are the characteristics of the market.

06:15.000 --> 06:18.000
How much does the market affect the choice of intermediaries?

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
What are the most important factors here?

06:20.000 --> 06:22.000
The first is, of course, the size of the market, its capacity.

06:22.000 --> 06:26.000
How much can you sell where you want to organize your intermediaries?

06:26.000 --> 06:28.000
This is a very important factor.

06:28.000 --> 06:33.000
If you find only one or two clients, or three, then it is certainly not a sale.

06:33.000 --> 06:36.000
Is it worth creating a revenue network for such sales?

06:36.000 --> 06:39.000
Therefore, before creating a revenue network,

06:39.000 --> 06:44.000
you need to assess the capacity of this region, or this industry, or this client group.

06:44.000 --> 06:47.000
We will see how to do it.

06:47.000 --> 06:49.000
Geographical scatter.

06:49.000 --> 06:54.000
Of course, it is important how far you will need to deliver goods.

06:54.000 --> 06:57.000
How often can transport go there?

06:57.000 --> 07:00.000
How will you deliver this product?

07:00.000 --> 07:06.000
All this is important so that the product is constantly presented in this revenue network.

07:06.000 --> 07:09.000
Otherwise, what is the point of developing it?

07:09.000 --> 07:13.000
The volume of purchases on this market.

07:13.000 --> 07:19.000
If we look at the market capacity, then how much sales are possible, we assess.

07:19.000 --> 07:26.000
And the volume of purchases, how many people have the opportunity to buy this product,

07:26.000 --> 07:29.000
how many of them will be able to buy it.

07:29.000 --> 07:35.000
And the main thing is that this characteristic is assessed in the monetary equivalent, not in the artificial one.

07:35.000 --> 07:39.000
Another point is the nature of demand, seasonality.

07:39.000 --> 07:44.000
This must be taken into account, because each product in each region can have its own specifics.

07:44.000 --> 07:48.000
Imagine you sell scooters or motorcycles.

07:48.000 --> 07:51.000
And one thing is that you sell them in the north,

07:51.000 --> 07:56.000
and you can ride them for two months a year.

07:56.000 --> 08:02.000
Or this is the Krasnodar Territory, where it is warm, and winter lasts for a maximum of three months.

08:02.000 --> 08:06.000
And all the other nine months you can easily sell your product.

08:06.000 --> 08:14.000
That is why you need to take into account the seasonality, how much seasonality affects this market.

08:14.000 --> 08:17.000
Do you need an intermediary here in this case?

08:17.000 --> 08:22.000
So, taking into account all these factors, of course, you need to build a revenue network,

08:22.000 --> 08:24.000
choose your intermediaries.

08:24.000 --> 08:28.000
In the workbook, you can see the block of the scheme for choosing the distribution channels.

08:28.000 --> 08:32.000
There you can recheck yourself, if you already have a revenue network,

08:32.000 --> 08:34.000
whether you have organized it correctly,

08:34.000 --> 08:41.000
or if you have a new product, then you can determine which system is best for selling your product.

08:41.000 --> 08:44.000
Now we will consider the method of assessing clients.

08:44.000 --> 08:49.000
The method of assessing clients is related to the point that we talked about.

08:49.000 --> 08:55.000
It is very important to determine your intermediaries at the very first stage and assess them constantly.

08:55.000 --> 08:58.000
In the workbook, you have an example.

08:58.000 --> 09:02.000
This is a method of assessment, in which an assessment is carried out according to each criterion,

09:02.000 --> 09:05.000
a balance, and a weight coefficient is set.

09:05.000 --> 09:07.000
How does the method work?

09:07.000 --> 09:12.000
The first thing we do is clarify the criteria, because for each market the criteria can be specific.

09:12.000 --> 09:17.000
In the workbook, you will see the basic things that are there,

09:17.000 --> 09:22.000
but then you must adapt it to your company, to your market,

09:22.000 --> 09:26.000
because you may have specific criteria for assessment.

09:26.000 --> 09:29.000
Then an expert group is formed.

09:29.000 --> 09:32.000
The expert group consists of the following specialists.

09:32.000 --> 09:37.000
The first is the sales managers, the middle managers, the sales managers,

09:37.000 --> 09:43.000
supervisors, the commercial director, that is, those who are directly connected with the clients.

09:43.000 --> 09:46.000
The second group of experts is the marketers.

09:46.000 --> 09:51.000
They must be involved in order to assess the clients.

09:51.000 --> 09:56.000
Why? Because if all this is given to the merchants, what will they get?

09:56.000 --> 10:01.000
After all, they all have some kind of personal relationship with these companies.

10:01.000 --> 10:06.000
And the assessment, if it is carried out only on the one hand, will be somewhat subjective.

10:06.000 --> 10:11.000
That is why it is desirable that the marketers are present during the assessment in the same way.

10:11.000 --> 10:18.000
An expert group of 7-9 people is formed and points are given according to each criterion.

10:18.000 --> 10:21.000
The points are given from 1 to 10.

10:21.000 --> 10:24.000
One is the minimum point, 10 is the maximum.

10:24.000 --> 10:27.000
The points are given by each expert individually.

10:27.000 --> 10:30.000
Then the expert group determines the weight coefficients.

10:30.000 --> 10:31.000
What is it?

10:31.000 --> 10:38.000
It determines the weight of each criterion, which, in the general opinion, in the opinion of the majority,

10:38.000 --> 10:41.000
is the most important when assessing.

10:41.000 --> 10:44.000
That is, regardless of the companies, but the general ones.

10:44.000 --> 10:48.000
For example, for each situation, the development of the market will be important for its own criteria.

10:48.000 --> 10:51.000
And every time the weight coefficient will change.

10:51.000 --> 10:54.000
That is why the expert group determines the weight coefficient.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
In total, this can be done by 1.

10:56.000 --> 10:58.000
And, accordingly, the weight coefficients will be broken.

10:58.000 --> 10:59.000
What is done next?

10:59.000 --> 11:02.000
Next, the points of each expert are taken and averaged.

11:03.000 --> 11:07.000
Then you multiply the points by the weight according to each criterion.

11:07.000 --> 11:11.000
And then you add up and calculate the average arithmetic.

11:11.000 --> 11:17.000
The average arithmetic gives you the key to this client, to the assessment of this client.

11:17.000 --> 11:19.000
The key says the following.

11:19.000 --> 11:22.000
We have an assessment divided into 4 groups.

11:22.000 --> 11:27.000
If your client is in the first group, then you just need to refuse the service of this intermediary.

11:27.000 --> 11:30.000
If in the second group, then, in general, this is a standard client,

11:30.000 --> 11:36.000
but things are not going very well, so you need to check the weak points of this client and try to change them.

11:36.000 --> 11:38.000
If something changes, great.

11:38.000 --> 11:40.000
If not, then we also refuse.

11:40.000 --> 11:41.000
But gradually, not immediately.

11:41.000 --> 11:44.000
We are looking for a replacement and refuse.

11:44.000 --> 11:47.000
The third group is a group of optimal intermediaries,

11:47.000 --> 11:53.000
who work well, are stable, standard, give you a good enough effect.

11:54.000 --> 11:59.000
And for them, a standard package of various additional services.

11:59.000 --> 12:04.000
Service, warranty, technical, maybe some kind of support.

12:04.000 --> 12:07.000
Standard intermediaries, that is, to maintain relations.

12:07.000 --> 12:12.000
And the fourth group is the best intermediaries, you can say the gold ones,

12:12.000 --> 12:19.000
who give you the most turnover, work best with you,

12:19.000 --> 12:21.000
and additional preferences.

12:21.000 --> 12:25.000
That is, something better than others, so that they feel this support.

12:25.000 --> 12:28.000
If they do not feel it, then, accordingly, they can leave.

12:28.000 --> 12:30.000
If they leave, you will lose a lot.

12:30.000 --> 12:35.000
Therefore, here are constructive relations and constant preferences.

12:35.000 --> 12:40.000
This is such an assessment, it will help you to optimize the sales system.

12:40.000 --> 12:45.000
When we conducted such an assessment for the first time, the situation was very ambiguous.

12:45.000 --> 12:49.000
And our salespeople reacted very badly to the fact that they had to refuse someone.

12:49.000 --> 12:51.000
They were outraged and said that this was their job,

12:51.000 --> 12:54.000
that they had been establishing relations for a very long time.

12:54.000 --> 12:59.000
But after that, of course, we could not insist on this, it was our recommendation.

12:59.000 --> 13:04.000
But after we made the decision to refuse, everything turned out very well,

13:04.000 --> 13:09.000
because additional resources were not spent on ineffective intermediaries.

13:09.000 --> 13:15.000
And this is calls, business trips, transport logistics, and everything else.

13:15.000 --> 13:19.000
The work of the department has become more effective.

13:19.000 --> 13:25.000
Therefore, strive for such a group of intermediaries to be minimal.

13:25.000 --> 13:29.000
Now we will look at two methods that I promised to consider.

13:29.000 --> 13:33.000
This is the first method, the search for new clients by industry.

13:33.000 --> 13:36.000
According to the previous method, you have rejected some of the clients,

13:36.000 --> 13:38.000
now you need something in return.

13:38.000 --> 13:40.000
Let's look for new clients.

13:40.000 --> 13:44.000
The first method is to search by industry, and the second method is to consider by regions.

13:44.000 --> 13:47.000
The method of searching for new clients by industry.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.000
When is it applicable?

13:48.000 --> 13:52.000
It is applicable when your product is specific.

13:52.000 --> 13:53.000
For example, medical equipment.

13:53.000 --> 13:55.000
You can't sell it to anyone.

13:55.000 --> 14:00.000
You sell it to intermediaries who work with medical institutions, right?

14:00.000 --> 14:03.000
Or directly to medical institutions.

14:04.000 --> 14:09.000
Or, an example I will give is a chromatography.

14:09.000 --> 14:16.000
A chromatography is a device that decomposes gas and liquid mediums into components,

14:16.000 --> 14:18.000
into chemical elements.

14:18.000 --> 14:20.000
Where is it used?

14:20.000 --> 14:24.000
It is used in medical expertise, in sanitary and epidemiological supervision,

14:24.000 --> 14:28.000
in alcohol companies, in the oil and gas industry, in the oil and chemical industry.

14:28.000 --> 14:30.000
That is, there are many applications.

14:30.000 --> 14:38.000
At the time when we used this method, our chromatography was sold in the amount of 50-60 pieces per year.

14:38.000 --> 14:42.000
And mostly, these were budget organizations.

14:42.000 --> 14:45.000
Here is medical expertise, sanitary and epidemiological supervision.

14:45.000 --> 14:46.000
We worked with them.

14:46.000 --> 14:48.000
Everything was stable, but very little.

14:48.000 --> 14:52.000
Naturally, the question arose, how can we do this to sell more?

14:52.000 --> 14:56.000
Because the device was in the top part of our positions.

14:56.000 --> 14:58.000
Let's turn to the method.

14:58.000 --> 15:00.000
It is presented on the slide.

15:00.000 --> 15:03.000
The first thing that is done is the analysis of the product nomenclature.

15:03.000 --> 15:04.000
By company.

15:04.000 --> 15:05.000
What is it for?

15:05.000 --> 15:08.000
To select the key positions, the top positions.

15:08.000 --> 15:11.000
We must always optimize resources.

15:11.000 --> 15:14.000
Therefore, our task is to choose the main one.

15:14.000 --> 15:18.000
And first, for the main product, find new clients.

15:18.000 --> 15:20.000
And not to do it for the whole product at once.

15:20.000 --> 15:24.000
For the sake of optimization, we choose the top range.

15:25.000 --> 15:28.000
The next thing we do is to analyze the industry markets.

15:28.000 --> 15:30.000
That is, which markets we can sell to.

15:30.000 --> 15:35.000
And which of them are the most profitable or promising from our point of view.

15:35.000 --> 15:41.000
So, just by chromatography, we realized that there is still the oil and gas industry, the oil and chemical industry.

15:41.000 --> 15:43.000
For some reason, we have not worked on it yet.

15:43.000 --> 15:46.000
We decided to go this way.

15:46.000 --> 15:49.000
The next thing we did, and this is the next step in the method,

15:49.000 --> 15:53.000
is to go to the industry leader with a favorable offer.

15:53.000 --> 15:54.000
Why the leader?

15:54.000 --> 15:58.000
You know, it is always easier to start your activity with the leader.

15:58.000 --> 16:00.000
The image of the leader is very strong.

16:00.000 --> 16:08.000
New products are listened to, and any product you want to offer can enter your market faster.

16:08.000 --> 16:10.000
That is, you will reduce the time.

16:10.000 --> 16:12.000
And time is also money.

16:12.000 --> 16:16.000
So, what did we do, according to my example, with the chromatography?

16:16.000 --> 16:20.000
We just found a person sitting on the information streams.

16:20.000 --> 16:22.000
We turned to the Gazprom Institute,

16:22.000 --> 16:29.000
where there was a person collecting all the requests from the oil and gas industry.

16:29.000 --> 16:36.000
This person gave us some information that there is such a plant, Nizhnyakamsk Oil and Gas.

16:36.000 --> 16:41.000
This is almost a city plant, it is a huge plant, there are buses with stops inside.

16:41.000 --> 16:46.000
That is, it is a very large production, and it is dangerous for human life.

16:47.000 --> 16:54.000
People work in special clothes, in chemical-proof suits with gas masks, and so on.

16:54.000 --> 16:59.000
That is, production is really very dangerous there.

16:59.000 --> 17:05.000
The company's leader decided to automate the process to secure his people.

17:05.000 --> 17:09.000
That is, in order to prevent people from controlling the process,

17:09.000 --> 17:13.000
he decided to put chromatographers there,

17:13.000 --> 17:17.000
so that they would take the information and send it to the central control panel,

17:17.000 --> 17:20.000
where a person would already sit and control the situation.

17:20.000 --> 17:23.000
But there was one problem.

17:23.000 --> 17:27.000
There were a lot of chromatographers on the market, like any other production.

17:27.000 --> 17:29.000
But they could not make a choice. Why?

17:29.000 --> 17:37.000
They needed a very simple device that simply measures and distributes gas or liquid into components.

17:38.000 --> 17:43.000
And all the devices presented on the market had additional functions, additional services.

17:43.000 --> 17:45.000
But, as we know, there is nothing free,

17:45.000 --> 17:50.000
so additional functions and additional services required additional money.

17:50.000 --> 17:52.000
It's like a mobile phone.

17:52.000 --> 17:56.000
Before, we bought a phone just to make a call,

17:56.000 --> 18:00.000
and now we have a video camera, an MP3 player,

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
I don't know, there will be a TV soon, and so on.

18:02.000 --> 18:07.000
There are a lot of other functions that have nothing to do with the main thing.

18:07.000 --> 18:10.000
Here, it's exactly the same.

18:10.000 --> 18:13.000
Here, they were looking for a simple device,

18:13.000 --> 18:15.000
no one agreed to simplify it,

18:15.000 --> 18:18.000
and they needed such a company.

18:18.000 --> 18:23.000
The next step we took was to establish personal contacts.

18:23.000 --> 18:30.000
We went to this enterprise and asked them what requirements were necessary for the device

18:30.000 --> 18:33.000
that they wanted to put into their automatic process.

18:33.000 --> 18:37.000
We were sent the requirements, we consulted with our technologists, designers,

18:37.000 --> 18:42.000
and they said, yes, we can simplify the device without any problems, it's not difficult to do,

18:42.000 --> 18:46.000
yes, it will cost a little less, but it will not be a disadvantage for our company,

18:46.000 --> 18:52.000
because the number that this company requested was huge, it was 600 devices.

18:52.000 --> 18:55.000
At the same time, as I said, we sold 50-60 a year.

18:55.000 --> 18:58.000
That is, it was an order for many years.

18:59.000 --> 19:03.000
Naturally, our designers, technologists, our specialists did everything possible,

19:03.000 --> 19:09.000
presented the device, and then the next step was the presentation to the industry.

19:09.000 --> 19:12.000
That is, we came to the enterprise, agreed on a meeting,

19:12.000 --> 19:15.000
presented our product, which we can put,

19:15.000 --> 19:18.000
after which the contract for delivery was concluded,

19:18.000 --> 19:22.000
