Well, we have considered two methods for finding new clients.

27:15.000 --> 27:19.000
But before going to a particular market,

27:19.000 --> 27:25.000
it is necessary to accurately assess what target segments are in these markets,

27:25.000 --> 27:28.000
who our intermediaries will work with,

27:28.000 --> 27:31.000
who our product is aimed at.

27:31.000 --> 27:37.000
Here we will consider one of many methods of segmentation and selection of target segments.

27:37.000 --> 27:39.000
What is a segment?

27:39.000 --> 27:44.000
A segment is a group of buyers or a group of clients

27:44.000 --> 27:48.000
who present the same requirements for your product.

27:48.000 --> 27:50.000
Let's take, for example, the computer market.

27:50.000 --> 27:51.000
The simplest example.

27:51.000 --> 27:54.000
What groups of consumers exist in this market?

27:54.000 --> 28:00.000
There are home users, those who buy a computer for home.

28:00.000 --> 28:06.000
For example, for games, for watching movies, for working on the Internet, and so on.

28:06.000 --> 28:15.000
There are computer users who are in research institutes.

28:15.000 --> 28:22.000
There are users who buy computers for server organization, and so on.

28:22.000 --> 28:24.000
What is the point?

28:24.000 --> 28:28.000
Each group of these consumers has its own individual requirements for the product.

28:28.000 --> 28:34.000
There are designers who need special requirements, special computers, special power,

28:34.000 --> 28:37.000
their own requirements for RAM, and so on.

28:37.000 --> 28:44.000
When we form individual proposals for each group, this is segmentation.

28:44.000 --> 28:49.000
We target our product directly for this group of consumers.

28:49.000 --> 28:51.000
This optimizes our resources.

28:51.000 --> 28:56.000
Because we don't have to work on all target segments.

28:57.000 --> 29:01.000
There is no resource optimization, no directionality in this case.

29:01.000 --> 29:03.000
We lose resources and time.

29:03.000 --> 29:06.000
Let's look at one of the methods, as I said.

29:06.000 --> 29:11.000
In the slide and in the workbook, this method will be fully presented.

29:11.000 --> 29:12.000
You can refer to it.

29:12.000 --> 29:13.000
What is happening here?

29:13.000 --> 29:16.000
We take segmentation criteria.

29:16.000 --> 29:18.000
There are 10 of them.

29:18.000 --> 29:24.000
Each criteria evaluates possible segments.

29:24.000 --> 29:28.000
We select all possible segments on which we can offer our product.

29:28.000 --> 29:32.000
Then, each criteria evaluates.

29:32.000 --> 29:34.000
The evaluation is carried out on a 10-point scale.

29:34.000 --> 29:37.000
From 1 to 10, 10 is the maximum, 1 is the minimum.

29:37.000 --> 29:40.000
The weight criterion is also included.

29:40.000 --> 29:44.000
The weight coefficient is very interesting here.

29:44.000 --> 29:51.000
From 1 to 3, 1 is not a very important parameter, 2 is the middle parameter, and 3 is the high parameter.

29:51.000 --> 29:53.000
The evaluation is carried out.

29:53.000 --> 29:57.000
Then we multiply the weight by the weight.

29:57.000 --> 30:01.000
And we also subtract the middle arithmetic.

30:01.000 --> 30:05.000
Let's comment on the criteria for evaluation.

30:05.000 --> 30:08.000
The first is the number of segments.

30:08.000 --> 30:13.000
The number of segments is recommended to be evaluated in the money equivalent.

30:13.000 --> 30:18.000
Because the number of clients will be incorrect.

30:18.000 --> 30:23.000
Therefore, evaluate the possible sales volume in this segment.

30:23.000 --> 30:25.000
The more, the better.

30:25.000 --> 30:28.000
The availability of the segment is a very interesting criterion.

30:28.000 --> 30:32.000
The availability of the segment should be considered not only from the point of view of territorial availability.

30:32.000 --> 30:35.000
For example, to deliver an opportunity at a certain time.

30:35.000 --> 30:42.000
For example, in the Krasnoyarsk Territory, we have territories where navigation only happens once every six months.

30:42.000 --> 30:46.000
And there people also need products, household appliances, and everything.

30:47.000 --> 30:55.000
Therefore, the availability of the segment is considered, first, from the point of view of territorial availability, and second, from the point of view of entry barriers.

30:55.000 --> 30:59.000
Let's take, for example, the motorcycle market.

30:59.000 --> 31:03.000
Scooters, motorcycles, and so on.

31:03.000 --> 31:14.000
Now there is a program, a government, which implies the equipment of the Ministry of Internal Affairs, the Ministry of Emergencies and the Russian Army with motorcycles.

31:14.000 --> 31:16.000
Of course, a tender is announced.

31:16.000 --> 31:22.000
To win this tender, it is necessary to make a huge effort.

31:22.000 --> 31:26.000
And at the same time, an administrative resource is needed here.

31:26.000 --> 31:31.000
Because without it, we simply will not be able to participate in the tender and not win it.

31:31.000 --> 31:35.000
This is also an availability, this is an entry barrier to this market.

31:35.000 --> 31:37.000
In the same way, you can evaluate the network difference.

31:37.000 --> 31:46.000
To enter a particular network, we need to pay an entry bonus, we need to give an additional discount.

31:46.000 --> 31:49.000
How acceptable is this for us, the company must decide.

31:49.000 --> 31:52.000
This is also an entry barrier.

31:52.000 --> 31:55.000
This is also the availability of the segment.

31:55.000 --> 31:57.000
It is easiest to sell tents in a tray.

31:57.000 --> 32:00.000
But maybe it's not so interesting in terms of turnover, right?

32:00.000 --> 32:05.000
And the most difficult thing is to enter the network, but the turnover there, of course, will be incomparable.

32:05.000 --> 32:10.000
The next parameter, the next criterion of assessment is the stability of the segment.

32:10.000 --> 32:11.000
What is it?

32:11.000 --> 32:13.000
This is related to seasonality.

32:13.000 --> 32:18.000
Seasonality is when the volume of sales drops, then rises, but it is still there.

32:18.000 --> 32:22.000
However, the stability of the segment can be estimated like this.

32:22.000 --> 32:26.000
There is a market for half a year, and half a year it is not there at all.

32:26.000 --> 32:28.000
That is, there is no sale at all.

32:28.000 --> 32:31.000
This market is unstable.

32:31.000 --> 32:35.000
And here, of course, the less stable the market, the worse for the company.

32:35.000 --> 32:43.000
Why? Because it will have to form an additional assortment for production to ensure the stability of production and the stability of sales.

32:43.000 --> 32:49.000
Let's take the example of mosquito cream.

32:49.000 --> 32:52.000
When is it sold?

32:52.000 --> 32:58.000
It starts selling in May, probably ends in September, and the rest of the year it just does not sell.

32:58.000 --> 33:00.000
This is an unstable market.

33:00.000 --> 33:06.000
Accordingly, companies that are engaged in this product have to look for some additional products

33:06.000 --> 33:10.000
that will compensate for the shortcomings of production and sales.

33:10.000 --> 33:13.000
The next criterion is profitability.

33:13.000 --> 33:16.000
Profitability in the segment can be different.

33:16.000 --> 33:21.000
Let's take and consider examples of profitability in the budget industry.

33:21.000 --> 33:26.000
For example, we sell medical equipment in a budget clinic and in a commercial one.

33:26.000 --> 33:30.000
So, where do you think the profitability will be higher?

33:30.000 --> 33:37.000
Today, the situation is that the profitability is higher in the budget sector.

33:37.000 --> 33:43.000
Because the money invested in the budget allows you to spend it without choosing a particular company.

33:43.000 --> 33:50.000
But commercial companies count every penny and look where the offer is most profitable.

33:50.000 --> 33:55.000
Therefore, paradoxically, the profitability in the commercial segment will be lower.

33:55.000 --> 34:01.000
Naturally, the higher the profitability, the higher the point will be according to this criterion.

34:01.000 --> 34:04.000
The next criterion is the level of competition.

34:04.000 --> 34:08.000
Naturally, the higher the level of competition, the worse it is for the company,

34:08.000 --> 34:12.000
because it will have to spend additional resources to compete with competitors.

34:12.000 --> 34:16.000
But the evaluation of competition is also ambiguous.

34:16.000 --> 34:18.000
What do you think is better?

34:18.000 --> 34:22.000
When there are many competitors and they are medium or small.

34:22.000 --> 34:29.000
For example, there are 20-30 competitors in this segment, but they are of medium size or small.

34:29.000 --> 34:33.000
Or when there are only 3 competitors, but they are large.

34:33.000 --> 34:37.000
Of course, it is more difficult to enter the market where there are fewer competitors, but they are large.

34:37.000 --> 34:42.000
Why? Because they also set entry barriers,

34:42.000 --> 34:48.000
they are more likely to fall into a conspiracy and prevent other companies from entering the market.

34:48.000 --> 34:53.000
For example, I can give a telecommunications market, not the entire market, but the mobile communication market.

34:53.000 --> 34:59.000
You know, 3 main players are MTS, Vimble.com and Megafon.

34:59.000 --> 35:06.000
And these 3 players actually hardly let other companies enter this market.

35:06.000 --> 35:09.000
Actually, they are the largest, and others cannot get in there well.

35:10.000 --> 35:13.000
And this situation will continue for some time.

35:13.000 --> 35:16.000
Therefore, the higher the competition, the lower the score.

35:16.000 --> 35:19.000
Here the characteristic will be inverse.

35:19.000 --> 35:22.000
The next point is protection from competition.

35:22.000 --> 35:27.000
Protection from competition is the presence of at least one competitive advantage.

35:27.000 --> 35:30.000
Remember what a competitive advantage is?

35:30.000 --> 35:33.000
This is the difference at least some from your competitor.

35:33.000 --> 35:38.000
If you have it, if you can position yourself in this way,

35:38.000 --> 35:41.000
consider that there is a direct road to this market.

35:41.000 --> 35:45.000
If your product is so standardized that there is no difference,

35:45.000 --> 35:50.000
come up with it, create an additional service, additional services,

35:50.000 --> 35:55.000
something else that will additionally distinguish you from competitors.

35:55.000 --> 35:57.000
I will give an example here.

35:57.000 --> 36:00.000
The situation in the air conditioner market.

36:00.000 --> 36:05.000
When we were developing a home air conditioning system,

36:05.000 --> 36:07.000
we had the same situation.

36:07.000 --> 36:09.000
It was very difficult for us to enter the market.

36:09.000 --> 36:11.000
The product was practically standardized.

36:11.000 --> 36:18.000
And we thought how to stand out from the general mass of the strongest competitors and foreign manufacturers.

36:18.000 --> 36:19.000
And what did we come up with?

36:19.000 --> 36:24.000
We created an additional service for our intermediaries.

36:24.000 --> 36:25.000
They really liked it.

36:25.000 --> 36:27.000
What is this additional service?

36:27.000 --> 36:31.000
We asked our intermediaries, what worries you in our product?

36:31.000 --> 36:33.000
Why are you afraid to work with it?

36:33.000 --> 36:34.000
What did they say?

36:34.000 --> 36:39.000
We do not know its quality, we do not know how it fails, and so on.

36:39.000 --> 36:43.000
We know that the quality of foreign manufacturers is high.

36:43.000 --> 36:46.000
And we know nothing about your device, about your product.

36:46.000 --> 36:49.000
And words are just words, because the product is new on the market.

36:49.000 --> 36:53.000
Thus, we offered them to create an exchange fund.

36:53.000 --> 37:01.000
That is, 10% of the volume of the delivery, we offered additional air conditioners for free,

37:01.000 --> 37:04.000
on the terms of responsible storage.

37:04.000 --> 37:06.000
For what?

37:06.000 --> 37:11.000
So that if at least one device fails, they can instantly replace it,

37:11.000 --> 37:16.000
without thinking that you need to send it to the manufacturer, then repair it,

37:16.000 --> 37:18.000
then send it back again.

37:18.000 --> 37:24.000
This is all time, these are all additional difficulties that the client absolutely does not need,

37:24.000 --> 37:28.000
and they should not worry about it at the competent level of the service.

37:28.000 --> 37:31.000
Therefore, our clients really liked it.

37:31.000 --> 37:39.000
Thus, they were insured from such failures that would involve the client's disloyalty.

37:39.000 --> 37:42.000
This helped us to enter the market very quickly.

37:42.000 --> 37:48.000
In just 4 months, we have formed a system of distributors in the number of 42 companies

37:48.000 --> 37:53.000
