58:22.000 --> 58:25.000
the market may not be very interesting for us.

58:25.000 --> 58:30.000
The next criteria is attractiveness, that is, how well the market will develop.

58:30.000 --> 58:35.000
The first point is the number of people who are older than 18 years.

58:35.000 --> 58:39.000
Why? Because alcohol can be consumed only after the age of 18.

58:39.000 --> 58:42.000
Therefore, for us, of course, this parameter is very interesting.

58:42.000 --> 58:45.000
The next point is foreign investment in the region.

58:45.000 --> 58:47.000
Why is this important to us?

58:47.000 --> 58:50.000
A very interesting point for the elite alcohol market.

58:50.000 --> 58:54.000
It has a direct relationship to development.

58:54.000 --> 58:58.000
As soon as we see an increase in investment,

58:58.000 --> 59:03.000
we see that a very good situation is developing in the region.

59:03.000 --> 59:08.000
The better the market develops, the more income the population grows,

59:08.000 --> 59:12.000
the more they allow themselves pleasant things.

59:12.000 --> 59:15.000
The next point is the dynamics of the development of the region itself,

59:15.000 --> 59:18.000
the dynamics of the development of its retail product turnover,

59:18.000 --> 59:20.000
that is, how it grows.

59:20.000 --> 59:25.000
Look, for comparison, the Moscow market and the Nizhny Novgorod market.

59:25.000 --> 59:28.000
Two cities that are very different in themselves.

59:28.000 --> 59:32.000
Why? The Moscow market is potentially very large.

59:32.000 --> 59:36.000
There are a lot of customers who can buy this product.

59:36.000 --> 59:44.000
But its development dynamics are already very low compared to the dynamics of development in Nizhny Novgorod.

59:44.000 --> 59:46.000
I will give you some figures.

59:46.000 --> 59:51.000
The turnover of Moscow grows by 5-6% per year,

59:51.000 --> 59:57.000
and the turnover of Nizhny Novgorod grows by 30-35% per year.

59:57.000 --> 59:59.000
Look at the difference.

59:59.000 --> 01:00:01.000
Why is this important to us?

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:04.000
Because it is easier to enter the developing market,

01:00:04.000 --> 01:00:09.000
it is easier to develop there and it is easier to get up.

01:00:09.000 --> 01:00:12.000
There is not such a high level of competition.

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:17.000
That is why we assess the attractiveness of the region from two points of view.

01:00:17.000 --> 01:00:21.000
The potential can be compared with operational activity,

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:24.000
and the attractiveness with strategic.

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:27.000
We look at how we can develop in this region.

01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:29.000
The next point is the level of competition.

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:33.000
Of course, we also assess the level of competition.

01:00:33.000 --> 01:00:35.000
Expert assessment is carried out here.

01:00:35.000 --> 01:00:39.000
Commercial and marketing departments participate in expert assessment.

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:42.000
These are the departments that are somehow connected with the market.

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:45.000
The assessment is given from 1 to 9.

01:00:45.000 --> 01:00:48.000
Then the weight coefficients are set.

01:00:48.000 --> 01:00:54.000
Here, attention, the weight coefficient for the potential of the region should be equal to 1.

01:00:54.000 --> 01:01:00.000
And the weight coefficient for the attractiveness of the region should be equal to 1.

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:07.000
Then you multiply the numbers, calculate the average arithmetic and get the result.

01:01:07.000 --> 01:01:10.000
The slide shows the result of the assessment of the regions.

01:01:10.000 --> 01:01:16.000
There are 9 squares in which certain regions got after the assessment.

01:01:16.000 --> 01:01:23.000
Naturally, the squares under the number 1, 2, 3, 4 are the most attractive for work.

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:26.000
And you need to start with the first one.

01:01:26.000 --> 01:01:32.000
Why? Because there is a good average potential, but the development is much higher.

01:01:32.000 --> 01:01:36.000
The second square, where the potential is high and the level of development is high,

01:01:36.000 --> 01:01:40.000
but the level of competition is quite high, so it is a little more difficult to get there.

01:01:40.000 --> 01:01:47.000
Then there is the third square, where the potential is high, but the level of development is average.

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:54.000
And the fourth square, where both assessments were obtained at an average level, from 3 to 6 points.

01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:59.000
That is, you can get there, but this is most likely a perspective, work for the perspective.

01:01:59.000 --> 01:02:03.000
That is, at the moment you will not make big turns there.

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:06.000
But in the future, this is possible in a very promising market for sales.

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:11.000
Thus, the methodology helps to assess the attractiveness of certain regions,

01:02:11.000 --> 01:02:17.000
not only from the point of view of the current profit, but also from the point of view of the company's development in the future.

01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:20.000
Let's look at the stages of distribution development.

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:25.000
We have already considered that depending on the life cycle of the product,

01:02:25.000 --> 01:02:29.000
the distribution develops in different ways, it has its stages.

01:02:29.000 --> 01:02:37.000
Now we will look at some features that companies need to pay attention to when developing a distribution system.

01:02:37.000 --> 01:02:42.000
The development system has three main stages.

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:44.000
What are they characterized by?

01:02:44.000 --> 01:02:48.000
The first stage is when the company has just entered the market,

01:02:48.000 --> 01:02:51.000
the company itself, not the product, but the company, and begins to sell.

01:02:51.000 --> 01:02:52.000
How does it behave?

01:02:52.000 --> 01:02:56.000
It gains a large range because it has no other competitive advantages,

01:02:56.000 --> 01:03:02.000
and begins to recruit sales representatives or sales managers who offer this product on the market.

01:03:02.000 --> 01:03:07.000
They have a very large price list, as a rule, and they just sell.

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:13.000
Accordingly, the success of the company depends only on the sales managers themselves.

01:03:13.000 --> 01:03:15.000
They sold well, the company feels good.

01:03:15.000 --> 01:03:18.000
They could not work, which means it did not work.

01:03:18.000 --> 01:03:22.000
This is the very first stage of the company's development.

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:27.000
It inevitably has a place to be, and it is simply impossible to immediately jump to the third stage.

01:03:27.000 --> 01:03:30.000
Therefore, for some time the company works like this,

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:33.000
masters the market, understands its specifics.

01:03:33.000 --> 01:03:36.000
It is advisable not to stay at this stage for a long time,

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:40.000
because it is not the most effective, not the most attractive.

01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:47.000
The second stage of development begins when the company sets itself a task not only in terms of sales volume,

01:03:47.000 --> 01:03:50.000
but in terms of sales volume, in terms of the top range.

01:03:50.000 --> 01:03:53.000
The company often sharply reduces the range,

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:59.000
because it understands that the sales manager cannot focus on the entire range of the company.

01:03:59.000 --> 01:04:01.000
This is impossible and ineffective.

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:08.000
Usually, the range is reduced, and moreover, the top range is selected, which is best sold.

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:14.000
Tasks are set for it, and, accordingly, the sales manager already has two tasks in terms of sales volume.

01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:19.000
On the contrary, and in terms of sales volume, the top range.

01:04:19.000 --> 01:04:24.000
Yes, this is a good stage, the second stage is the development of the company.

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:26.000
Nevertheless, it has both advantages and disadvantages.

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:28.000
The first advantage is the speed.

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:31.000
You can create such a system very quickly.

01:04:31.000 --> 01:04:34.000
The second advantage is flexibility.

01:04:34.000 --> 01:04:39.000
It was not possible to work with one distributor, with the second, and the third is the operability.

01:04:39.000 --> 01:04:43.000
You can contact a particular company very quickly, solve issues, and so on.

01:04:43.000 --> 01:04:46.000
But, in fact, this stage has a lot of disadvantages.

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:47.000
Let's look at them.

01:04:47.000 --> 01:04:50.000
The first disadvantage is high competition among manufacturers.

01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:52.000
What we have already discussed today.

01:04:52.000 --> 01:04:58.000
Each dealer or distributor has many manufacturers.

01:04:58.000 --> 01:05:01.000
And inside, dealers or distributors compete with each other.

01:05:01.000 --> 01:05:06.000
Well, imagine, one company gives funds for promotion, the second, the third, the fifteenth,

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:09.000
and the dealer no longer knows what to do.

01:05:09.000 --> 01:05:12.000
He looks where it is more profitable, and sells.

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:14.000
And he is not particularly interested.

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:21.000
It is clear that your assortment is top-notch, so your task is to focus on your assortment.

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:26.000
To stand out among the many manufacturers that supply this product to him.

01:05:26.000 --> 01:05:30.000
The next disadvantage is the dependence on the leaders of the trading representatives.

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:31.000
What is it?

01:05:31.000 --> 01:05:34.000
In any company there are people who know how to sell well.

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:38.000
They mostly take a good client base, work at interest rates.

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:43.000
They are not very interested in the output of a new product, because they earn well on the existing one.

01:05:43.000 --> 01:05:47.000
They have established relations and work very well with them.

01:05:47.000 --> 01:05:49.000
What is the disadvantage for the company?

01:05:49.000 --> 01:05:51.000
They sell well.

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:53.000
The disadvantage is that you depend on them.

01:05:53.000 --> 01:05:58.000
If only this sales manager decides to leave your company, God forbid, the competitor,

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:01.000
then you think you have lost this client.

01:06:01.000 --> 01:06:04.000
This is what happened to us when we changed the distribution system.

01:06:04.000 --> 01:06:10.000
Some managers who worked in the catering segment,

01:06:11.000 --> 01:06:13.000
it is the most difficult to establish relations there,

01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:16.000
and we lost about 30% of the client base.

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:18.000
It was a very bad result.

01:06:18.000 --> 01:06:20.000
We had to restore everything again.

01:06:20.000 --> 01:06:23.000
Therefore, special attention should be paid to this.

01:06:23.000 --> 01:06:25.000
How to avoid the situation?

01:06:25.000 --> 01:06:27.000
Give an assistant.

01:06:27.000 --> 01:06:34.000
Let the second assistant, a young manager, go and learn together with this leader.

01:06:35.000 --> 01:06:39.000
This way he will gain experience and a base,

01:06:39.000 --> 01:06:43.000
and establish relations with your key clients.

01:06:43.000 --> 01:06:47.000
The drain of regional products is also a big disadvantage.

01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:48.000
Why?

01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:50.000
You have made a sales system,

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:52.000
you have two or three distributors,

01:06:52.000 --> 01:06:54.000
they start to compete with each other.

01:06:54.000 --> 01:06:56.000
They gain a large volume,

01:06:56.000 --> 01:06:57.000
at large discounts,

01:06:57.000 --> 01:06:59.000
then they cannot sell it,

01:06:59.000 --> 01:07:03.000
and they start to sell it at low prices in the regions.

01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:04.000
This is very bad,

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:09.000
because they create additional competition for those who work there.

01:07:09.000 --> 01:07:12.000
This, of course, must be avoided.

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:14.000
How?

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:16.000
Structuring the sales system clearly

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:19.000
and trying not to make price changes.

01:07:19.000 --> 01:07:21.000
It is difficult to control,

01:07:21.000 --> 01:07:24.000
but if possible, you need to try to do it.

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:27.000
The next disadvantage is the dependence on the human factor.

01:07:27.000 --> 01:07:32.000
This point often intersects with the leaders of the trading representatives.

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:34.000
You actually depend on them,

01:07:34.000 --> 01:07:36.000
depend on the person.

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:40.000
And you need to create a system that will not depend on the person,

01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:42.000
or will not depend on the maximum,

01:07:42.000 --> 01:07:44.000
as little as possible.

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:46.000
Then your system will work like a clock.

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:51.000
That is why it goes to the third stage of distribution development.

01:07:51.000 --> 01:07:53.000
What is this third stage?

01:07:53.000 --> 01:07:55.000
When we set ourselves other tasks,

01:07:55.000 --> 01:07:57.000
we set ourselves tasks for the volume of sales,

01:07:57.000 --> 01:07:59.000
for the top range,

01:07:59.000 --> 01:08:01.000
and also a plan for the marginal income.

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:03.000
Why is this important?

01:08:03.000 --> 01:08:07.000
Imagine you set a task for your regional managers.

01:08:07.000 --> 01:08:10.000
Here is the volume of sales, here is the top range.

01:08:10.000 --> 01:08:11.000
You have to sell it.

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:13.000
He sells.

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:16.000
He tries to give more discounts to get more volume.

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:18.000
Conduct some additional programs.

01:08:18.000 --> 01:08:20.000
Is it profitable for the company?

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:22.000
Most likely not.

01:08:22.000 --> 01:08:26.000
Because the marginal income is eaten up by these programs,

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:28.000
by these budgets, by these discounts.

01:08:28.000 --> 01:08:30.000
Why does this happen?

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:32.000
Because your manager is motivated

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:34.000
not to earn money,

01:08:34.000 --> 01:08:36.000
not to earn money,

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:38.000
but only to increase the volume of sales.

01:08:38.000 --> 01:08:41.000
That is why when the company goes to the third stage

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:43.000
and thinks about the marginal income,

01:08:43.000 --> 01:08:46.000
the third stage of development begins.

01:08:46.000 --> 01:08:50.000
A more serious, more stable, more competent.

01:08:56.000 --> 01:09:00.000
Why is it important to set a task for the volume of sales?

01:09:05.000 --> 01:09:10.000
Now we will look at the method of forming the volume of sales

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:12.000
or sales forecast.

01:09:12.000 --> 01:09:14.000
This is one of the key issues

01:09:14.000 --> 01:09:16.000
when forming a household network

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:18.000
and, accordingly, when optimizing it.

01:09:18.000 --> 01:09:21.000
When we set a task for the volume of sales,

01:09:21.000 --> 01:09:24.000
of course, we want the volume to be greater.

01:09:24.000 --> 01:09:26.000
Let's look at the method

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:28.000
developed by Jean-Jacques Lambin

01:09:28.000 --> 01:09:31.000
to optimize the company's turnover.

01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:33.000
How can it be increased?

01:09:33.000 --> 01:09:38.000
At what steps can we increase the volume of sales?

01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:40.000
Let's go through the ladder,

01:09:40.000 --> 01:09:42.000
which is presented on the slide.

01:09:42.000 --> 01:09:44.000
The first thing we can do

01:09:44.000 --> 01:09:47.000
is to strengthen the company's position.

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:50.000
We think that everything is fine in the company.

01:09:50.000 --> 01:09:52.000
We have a sales department,

01:09:52.000 --> 01:09:55.000
we have a sufficient number of managers,

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:57.000
they are qualified,

01:09:57.000 --> 01:09:59.000
they work competently,

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:01.000
their functions are not duplicated.

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:05.000
Believe me, such a perfect situation is very rare.

01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:09.000
Nevertheless, optimization in this area

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:12.000
allows to increase the company's turnover

01:10:12.000 --> 01:10:14.000
up to 42%.

01:10:14.000 --> 01:10:16.000
This is only in my practice,

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:18.000
maybe somewhere there is more.

01:10:18.000 --> 01:10:20.000
I will give an example

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:22.000
of how the sales organization works

01:10:22.000 --> 01:10:24.000
among managers in commercial departments.

01:10:24.000 --> 01:10:27.000
One of the companies produced plastic windows.

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:31.000
The profiles for plastic windows were collected and sold.

01:10:31.000 --> 01:10:34.000
The company was organized by a person

01:10:34.000 --> 01:10:37.000
who worked before in a research institute.

01:10:37.000 --> 01:10:41.000
He brought a team of his colleagues,

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:45.000
who successfully found the equipment,

01:10:45.000 --> 01:10:48.000
installed it, launched the technology,

01:10:48.000 --> 01:10:50.000
organized production.

01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:52.000
They were great specialists in this.

01:10:52.000 --> 01:10:54.000
But as soon as the question of sales arose,

01:10:54.000 --> 01:10:56.000
the question of the product was raised.

01:10:56.000 --> 01:10:58.000
It was 8 years ago.

01:10:58.000 --> 01:11:00.000
It was the most active development

01:11:00.000 --> 01:11:02.000
of this market, the plastic window market.

01:11:02.000 --> 01:11:04.000
There were not so many competitors then.

01:11:04.000 --> 01:11:06.000
But the manager asked a question,

01:11:06.000 --> 01:11:08.000
why is it not being sold?

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:10.000
They invited a consultant.

01:11:10.000 --> 01:11:12.000
The consultant looked at the company,

01:11:12.000 --> 01:11:14.000
looked at how people work,

01:11:14.000 --> 01:11:15.000
and said,

01:11:15.000 --> 01:11:18.000
you just don't have competent sales managers.

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:19.000
He said, how come?

01:11:19.000 --> 01:11:22.000
There are guys, competent, with a scientific degree,

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:23.000
and so on.

01:11:23.000 --> 01:11:24.000
What about them?

01:11:24.000 --> 01:11:25.000
They can't sell.

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:28.000
What was the answer?

01:11:28.000 --> 01:11:29.000
Of course not.

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:31.000
Sales should be done professionally

01:11:31.000 --> 01:11:33.000
by completely different people.

01:11:33.000 --> 01:11:35.000
They should be ambitious,

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:36.000
purposeful.

01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:38.000
And a scientific degree is not necessary here.

01:11:38.000 --> 01:11:40.000
The main thing is that he can

01:11:40.000 --> 01:11:42.000
present the product and sell it competently.

01:11:42.000 --> 01:11:44.000
And this is actually a talent needed.

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:45.000
Or at least skills.

01:11:45.000 --> 01:11:46.000
Very good skills.

01:11:46.000 --> 01:11:48.000
That's why the product was not sold.

01:11:48.000 --> 01:11:50.000
What did the consultant advise?

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:52.000
To hire sales managers.

01:11:52.000 --> 01:11:54.000
They found three people,

01:11:54.000 --> 01:11:56.000
three young people,

01:11:56.000 --> 01:11:59.000
developed a good motivation system

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:01.000
that really motivated them,

01:12:01.000 --> 01:12:03.000
and launched them into the field.

01:12:03.000 --> 01:12:05.000
What is it called?

01:12:05.000 --> 01:12:07.000
The result was stunning.

01:12:07.000 --> 01:12:09.000
In three months,

01:12:09.000 --> 01:12:11.000
so many orders were collected

01:12:11.000 --> 01:12:13.000
that the production stopped doing well.

01:12:14.000 --> 01:12:16.000
Of course,

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:19.000
the company bought additional equipment,

01:12:19.000 --> 01:12:22.000
and now it is one of the leaders

01:12:22.000 --> 01:12:24.000
in the North-West region

01:12:24.000 --> 01:12:26.000
in the production of plastic windows.

01:12:26.000 --> 01:12:31.000
Only optimization in the commercial department

01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:33.000
allowed to achieve such great results.

01:12:33.000 --> 01:12:35.000
That's why you need to approach

01:12:35.000 --> 01:12:37.000
the sales organization very competently.

01:12:37.000 --> 01:12:39.000
If everything is great there,

01:12:39.000 --> 01:12:41.000
and there is nothing to improve,

01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:43.000
then we move on.

01:12:43.000 --> 01:12:45.000
We attack competitors.

01:12:45.000 --> 01:12:47.000
You can attack competitors in different ways.

01:12:47.000 --> 01:12:49.000
You can produce a duplicate product,

01:12:49.000 --> 01:12:51.000
you can lower prices,

01:12:51.000 --> 01:12:53.000
you can fix all kinds of obstacles,

01:12:53.000 --> 01:12:55.000
launch rumors.

01:12:55.000 --> 01:12:57.000
There are many ways to fight competitors.

01:12:57.000 --> 01:12:59.000
There is one but.

01:12:59.000 --> 01:13:01.000
If you are a strong company in the market,

01:13:01.000 --> 01:13:03.000
you can afford this luxury of fighting competitors.

01:13:03.000 --> 01:13:05.000
If your company is not so strong,

01:13:05.000 --> 01:13:07.000
not so large at the moment,

01:13:07.000 --> 01:13:09.000
it is better not to get involved in this fight.

01:13:09.000 --> 01:13:11.000
Because competitors will crush you

01:13:11.000 --> 01:13:13.000
if they are stronger than you.

