01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:49.000
I would like to focus

01:15:49.000 --> 01:15:51.000
on the practical application of this matrix

01:15:51.000 --> 01:15:53.000
for the accuracy of the sales forecast.

01:15:53.000 --> 01:15:55.000
This is what we do

01:15:55.000 --> 01:15:57.000
in our company today.

01:15:57.000 --> 01:15:59.000
How can it be applied?

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:01.000
I'll briefly remind you

01:16:01.000 --> 01:16:03.000
what Ansofa matrix is.

01:16:03.000 --> 01:16:05.000
Ansofa matrix is divided into fields.

01:16:05.000 --> 01:16:07.000
This is the old market â€“ the old product.

01:16:07.000 --> 01:16:09.000
And the new market â€“ the new product.

01:16:09.000 --> 01:16:11.000
Accordingly, there is a strategy

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:13.000
to work on this product

01:16:13.000 --> 01:16:15.000
or on this segment

01:16:15.000 --> 01:16:17.000
to cross these fields.

01:16:17.000 --> 01:16:19.000
The old market â€“ the old product.

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:21.000
We just penetrate the market deeper,

01:16:21.000 --> 01:16:23.000
increase the turnover

01:16:23.000 --> 01:16:25.000
and increase the sales volume.

01:16:25.000 --> 01:16:27.000
We increase the turnover

01:16:27.000 --> 01:16:29.000
of existing clients

01:16:29.000 --> 01:16:31.000
for the existing product.

01:16:31.000 --> 01:16:33.000
If we choose the old market â€“ the new product,

01:16:33.000 --> 01:16:35.000
it means that we offer

01:16:35.000 --> 01:16:37.000
the existing client a new product.

01:16:37.000 --> 01:16:39.000
This strategy is called product development.

01:16:39.000 --> 01:16:41.000
If we sell the old product

01:16:41.000 --> 01:16:43.000
on the new market,

01:16:43.000 --> 01:16:45.000
we are looking for new clients

01:16:45.000 --> 01:16:47.000
for the existing assortment.

01:16:47.000 --> 01:16:49.000
This is called market development.

01:16:49.000 --> 01:16:51.000
If we sell new products on the new market,

01:16:51.000 --> 01:16:53.000
this is a diversification strategy.

01:16:53.000 --> 01:16:55.000
We change everything.

01:16:55.000 --> 01:16:57.000
We change the product, we change the market.

01:16:57.000 --> 01:16:59.000
This is the most risky strategy.

01:16:59.000 --> 01:17:01.000
But sometimes,

01:17:01.000 --> 01:17:03.000
if it works,

01:17:03.000 --> 01:17:05.000
it can be the most profitable.

01:17:05.000 --> 01:17:07.000
How to apply this matrix

01:17:07.000 --> 01:17:09.000
to sell the product?

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:11.000
We do it as follows.

01:17:13.000 --> 01:17:15.000
We divide our clients

01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:17.000
on the new clients

01:17:17.000 --> 01:17:19.000
with whom we plan to sign the contract

01:17:19.000 --> 01:17:21.000
and on the existing ones.

01:17:21.000 --> 01:17:23.000
Then we choose the key clients

01:17:23.000 --> 01:17:25.000
according to the rules of Pareto.

01:17:25.000 --> 01:17:27.000
These are the main clients

01:17:27.000 --> 01:17:29.000
that make the main turnover.

01:17:29.000 --> 01:17:31.000
Then we ask our commercial managers

01:17:31.000 --> 01:17:33.000
to predict the sales

01:17:33.000 --> 01:17:35.000
of the existing clients.

01:17:41.000 --> 01:17:43.000
Then they predict

01:17:43.000 --> 01:17:45.000
how they will offer

01:17:45.000 --> 01:17:47.000
our new product

01:17:47.000 --> 01:17:49.000
to the existing clients

01:17:49.000 --> 01:17:51.000
and how they will sell it.

01:17:51.000 --> 01:17:53.000
Of course,

01:17:53.000 --> 01:17:55.000
we need to have additional negotiations.

01:17:55.000 --> 01:17:57.000
But we don't have many clients.

01:17:57.000 --> 01:17:59.000
We only choose the key ones.

01:17:59.000 --> 01:18:01.000
The next step

01:18:01.000 --> 01:18:03.000
is to consider

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:05.000
whether they can offer

01:18:05.000 --> 01:18:07.000
our existing products

01:18:07.000 --> 01:18:09.000
to the new potential clients.

01:18:09.000 --> 01:18:11.000
They also make a sales forecast.

01:18:11.000 --> 01:18:13.000
We have statistics

01:18:13.000 --> 01:18:15.000
for the previous clients.

01:18:15.000 --> 01:18:17.000
We look at how they bought the product,

01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:19.000
what was the increase in turnover.

01:18:19.000 --> 01:18:21.000
We compare

01:18:21.000 --> 01:18:23.000
similar regions and similar clients.

01:18:23.000 --> 01:18:25.000
It helps us to build a figure.

01:18:25.000 --> 01:18:27.000
When we have diversification

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:29.000
of new products and new clients,

01:18:29.000 --> 01:18:31.000
it is actually an intuition.

01:18:31.000 --> 01:18:33.000
The manager

01:18:33.000 --> 01:18:35.000
determines

01:18:35.000 --> 01:18:37.000
how much he can sell

01:18:37.000 --> 01:18:39.000
the product to the new clients.

01:18:39.000 --> 01:18:41.000
Then we add

01:18:41.000 --> 01:18:43.000
the figures to this matrix

01:18:43.000 --> 01:18:45.000
and multiply it

01:18:45.000 --> 01:18:47.000
by the percentage of the new product

01:18:47.000 --> 01:18:49.000
that was presented on your slide.

01:18:49.000 --> 01:18:51.000
We multiply the percentage

01:18:51.000 --> 01:18:53.000
of the new product by 95%.

01:18:53.000 --> 01:18:55.000
There can be 5% error,

01:18:55.000 --> 01:18:57.000
although managers

01:18:57.000 --> 01:18:59.000
are very good at

01:18:59.000 --> 01:19:01.000
determining the sales volume

01:19:01.000 --> 01:19:03.000
for the key clients.

01:19:03.000 --> 01:19:05.000
When we buy a new product

01:19:05.000 --> 01:19:07.000
from the old clients,

01:19:07.000 --> 01:19:09.000
we take the coefficient 65.

01:19:09.000 --> 01:19:11.000
60 or 70,

01:19:11.000 --> 01:19:13.000
we take the average one, 65.

01:19:13.000 --> 01:19:15.000
We get the same figure.

01:19:15.000 --> 01:19:17.000
We reduce the figure by 3-5%.

01:19:17.000 --> 01:19:19.000
The next step is

01:19:19.000 --> 01:19:21.000
to buy the old product from the new clients.

01:19:21.000 --> 01:19:23.000
The accuracy of the forecast is reduced

01:19:23.000 --> 01:19:25.000
because we haven't worked with these clients yet.

01:19:25.000 --> 01:19:27.000
Nevertheless,

01:19:27.000 --> 01:19:29.000
we multiply this figure by 45%.

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:31.000
We subtract 55%.

01:19:33.000 --> 01:19:35.000
New clients, new products

01:19:35.000 --> 01:19:37.000
have an accuracy

01:19:37.000 --> 01:19:39.000
of 10-15%.

01:19:39.000 --> 01:19:41.000
The numbers we get

