The method is a compilation

01:24:37.000 --> 01:24:39.000
of two methods of quality assessment.

01:24:39.000 --> 01:24:41.000
These methods are known,

01:24:41.000 --> 01:24:43.000
but their combination

01:24:43.000 --> 01:24:45.000
gives the smallest error

01:24:45.000 --> 01:24:47.000
when calculating the forecast.

01:24:47.000 --> 01:24:49.000
I will give an example

01:24:49.000 --> 01:24:51.000
of split systems

01:24:51.000 --> 01:24:53.000
with which we started

01:24:53.000 --> 01:24:55.000
the development of this technique.

01:24:55.000 --> 01:24:57.000
The first thing to do

01:24:57.000 --> 01:24:59.000
is to analyze the demand

01:24:59.000 --> 01:25:01.000
and supply on the market.

01:25:01.000 --> 01:25:03.000
This is the work of marketologists

01:25:03.000 --> 01:25:05.000
who have to show

01:25:05.000 --> 01:25:07.000
which market is the most promising,

01:25:07.000 --> 01:25:09.000
where to go,

01:25:09.000 --> 01:25:11.000
where the largest sales volume

01:25:11.000 --> 01:25:13.000
can be,

01:25:13.000 --> 01:25:15.000
what are the trends of development,

01:25:15.000 --> 01:25:17.000
and how interesting it is to work there.

01:25:17.000 --> 01:25:19.000
The next step is to select

01:25:19.000 --> 01:25:21.000
the target segments.

01:25:21.000 --> 01:25:23.000
We have just considered the method

01:25:23.000 --> 01:25:25.000
of selecting the target segments.

01:25:25.000 --> 01:25:27.000
We select them and make a sales forecast

01:25:27.000 --> 01:25:29.000
only for the target segments.

01:25:29.000 --> 01:25:31.000
We do not need a sales forecast

01:25:31.000 --> 01:25:33.000
for the general market,

01:25:33.000 --> 01:25:35.000
because we will promote the product

01:25:35.000 --> 01:25:37.000
only for the target segments.

01:25:37.000 --> 01:25:39.000
Everything else will be additional sales.

01:25:39.000 --> 01:25:41.000
It will be those 20%

01:25:41.000 --> 01:25:43.000
that do not make up the main turnover of the company.

01:25:43.000 --> 01:25:45.000
The next thing to do

01:25:45.000 --> 01:25:47.000
is to select the calculation methods.

01:25:47.000 --> 01:25:49.000
We have made a compilation

01:25:49.000 --> 01:25:51.000
of even three methods,

01:25:51.000 --> 01:25:53.000
but the first method, the normative calculation,

01:25:53.000 --> 01:25:55.000
did not show itself well

01:25:55.000 --> 01:25:57.000
in this situation.

01:25:57.000 --> 01:25:59.000
I will explain why.

01:25:59.000 --> 01:26:01.000
Statistical methods work very well

01:26:01.000 --> 01:26:03.000
in stable markets.

01:26:03.000 --> 01:26:05.000
When it is clear how much and what will be consumed,

01:26:05.000 --> 01:26:07.000
what time and what price,

01:26:07.000 --> 01:26:09.000
then it is easy to calculate.

01:26:09.000 --> 01:26:11.000
You can calculate the consumption of bread,

01:26:11.000 --> 01:26:13.000
milk, because it is a product

01:26:13.000 --> 01:26:15.000
that will not go somewhere.

01:26:15.000 --> 01:26:17.000
There will be a small error.

01:26:17.000 --> 01:26:19.000
But the products on the market

01:26:19.000 --> 01:26:21.000
that are highly competitive

01:26:21.000 --> 01:26:23.000
and, moreover,

01:26:23.000 --> 01:26:25.000
unstable situation,

01:26:25.000 --> 01:26:27.000
constantly changing,

01:26:27.000 --> 01:26:29.000
such a method does not suit.

01:26:29.000 --> 01:26:31.000
I will give an example.

01:26:31.000 --> 01:26:33.000
Once we came to a conference.

01:26:33.000 --> 01:26:35.000
One professor of the University of St. Petersburg

01:26:35.000 --> 01:26:37.000
developed a wonderful method

01:26:37.000 --> 01:26:39.000
of trend assessment of sales forecast.

01:26:39.000 --> 01:26:41.000
He presented it

01:26:41.000 --> 01:26:43.000
and said that the accuracy

01:26:43.000 --> 01:26:45.000
of his method

01:26:45.000 --> 01:26:47.000
is only 5% error.

01:26:47.000 --> 01:26:49.000
It was perfect.

01:26:49.000 --> 01:26:51.000
We just introduced a new product

01:26:51.000 --> 01:26:53.000
to the market, and we were very interested

01:26:53.000 --> 01:26:55.000
in this method, because we needed

01:26:55.000 --> 01:26:57.000
to predict the sales as accurately as possible.

01:26:57.000 --> 01:26:59.000
We were ready to buy this method.

01:26:59.000 --> 01:27:01.000
We approached him

01:27:01.000 --> 01:27:03.000
and asked what features

01:27:03.000 --> 01:27:05.000
are present in the application of this method.

01:27:05.000 --> 01:27:07.000
He told us that everything is fine,

01:27:07.000 --> 01:27:09.000
everything is fine, it will work.

01:27:09.000 --> 01:27:11.000
But one condition.

01:27:11.000 --> 01:27:13.000
In order for this method to work,

01:27:13.000 --> 01:27:15.000
you must enter the input data

01:27:15.000 --> 01:27:17.000
for sales

01:27:17.000 --> 01:27:19.000
for the previous 50 years

01:27:19.000 --> 01:27:21.000
per month.

01:27:21.000 --> 01:27:23.000
Can you imagine where such data

01:27:23.000 --> 01:27:25.000
from our market, which has just been formed,

01:27:25.000 --> 01:27:27.000
come from? We do not have so much time.

01:27:27.000 --> 01:27:29.000
He says,

01:27:29.000 --> 01:27:31.000
then the error will be greater.

01:27:31.000 --> 01:27:33.000
For example, 40 to 60.

01:27:33.000 --> 01:27:35.000
We can predict without any method.

01:27:35.000 --> 01:27:37.000
Therefore, of course,

01:27:37.000 --> 01:27:39.000
mathematical models are applicable,

01:27:39.000 --> 01:27:41.000
but it all depends on the input data

01:27:41.000 --> 01:27:43.000
that you entered.

01:27:43.000 --> 01:27:45.000
And you still enter it yourself,

01:27:45.000 --> 01:27:47.000
it turns out to be of high quality.

01:27:47.000 --> 01:27:49.000
That is why only high-quality estimates

01:27:49.000 --> 01:27:51.000
work on new markets, on unstable ones.

01:27:51.000 --> 01:27:53.000
They give less error,

01:27:53.000 --> 01:27:55.000
more competent people

01:27:55.000 --> 01:27:57.000
give information about how to assess

01:27:57.000 --> 01:27:59.000
the sales forecast.

01:27:59.000 --> 01:28:01.000
Well, two more methods that we used

01:28:01.000 --> 01:28:03.000
as a result.

01:28:03.000 --> 01:28:05.000
What is this method?

01:28:05.000 --> 01:28:07.000
We chose three reference groups.

01:28:07.000 --> 01:28:09.000
The first is the company management,

01:28:09.000 --> 01:28:11.000
the second is sales managers,

01:28:11.000 --> 01:28:13.000
and the third is our clients,

01:28:13.000 --> 01:28:15.000
who are available.

01:28:15.000 --> 01:28:17.000
And, accordingly, we asked them a question.

01:28:17.000 --> 01:28:19.000
Please predict the sales volume

01:28:19.000 --> 01:28:21.000
of split systems

01:28:21.000 --> 01:28:23.000
for the next year

01:28:23.000 --> 01:28:25.000
and

01:28:25.000 --> 01:28:27.000
the total market volume.

01:28:27.000 --> 01:28:29.000
Accordingly,

01:28:29.000 --> 01:28:31.000
the management gave us its figure,

01:28:31.000 --> 01:28:33.000
that is, the vision

01:28:33.000 --> 01:28:35.000
that the managers had.

01:28:35.000 --> 01:28:37.000
The management

01:28:37.000 --> 01:28:39.000
sets up this process

01:28:39.000 --> 01:28:41.000
and they are the main marketologists.

01:28:41.000 --> 01:28:43.000
Therefore,

01:28:43.000 --> 01:28:45.000
it is rare to put

01:28:45.000 --> 01:28:47.000
unreasonable numbers.

01:28:47.000 --> 01:28:49.000
People who manage the process

01:28:49.000 --> 01:28:51.000
usually know what they are doing.

01:28:51.000 --> 01:28:53.000
The second point is

01:28:53.000 --> 01:28:55.000
our sales managers.

01:28:55.000 --> 01:28:57.000
They predicted,

01:28:57.000 --> 01:28:59.000
of course, their sales forecast was less,

01:28:59.000 --> 01:29:01.000
but we got the figure.

01:29:01.000 --> 01:29:03.000
The third group is our clients,

01:29:03.000 --> 01:29:05.000
who also gave us the figure.

01:29:05.000 --> 01:29:07.000
So, you know what an interesting situation we got.

01:29:07.000 --> 01:29:09.000
The difference in the forecast was 12.5%.

01:29:09.000 --> 01:29:11.000
The top were managers.

01:29:11.000 --> 01:29:13.000
The lowest forecast

01:29:13.000 --> 01:29:15.000
was given by sales managers.

01:29:15.000 --> 01:29:17.000
And approximately in the middle,

01:29:17.000 --> 01:29:19.000
but not exactly in the middle,

01:29:19.000 --> 01:29:21.000
but 5% of the forecast

01:29:21.000 --> 01:29:23.000
was given by clients.

01:29:23.000 --> 01:29:25.000
And the difference between clients

01:29:25.000 --> 01:29:27.000
and sales managers

01:29:27.000 --> 01:29:29.000
was 12.5%.

01:29:29.000 --> 01:29:31.000
We did not stop at the reached number.

01:29:31.000 --> 01:29:33.000
We decided to double-check our figures

01:29:33.000 --> 01:29:35.000
and used the Delphi method.

01:29:35.000 --> 01:29:37.000
The Delphi method is a very interesting method,

01:29:37.000 --> 01:29:39.000
when experts are invited

01:29:39.000 --> 01:29:41.000
to assess the sales forecast.

01:29:41.000 --> 01:29:43.000
Accordingly, we chose experts

01:29:43.000 --> 01:29:45.000
who have been working on the market for a long time,

01:29:45.000 --> 01:29:47.000
who are really the leaders of the industry.

01:29:47.000 --> 01:29:49.000
There were 5 of them.

01:29:49.000 --> 01:29:51.000
We asked them the same question.

01:29:51.000 --> 01:29:53.000
Please predict the volume of sales

01:29:53.000 --> 01:29:55.000
of the industry by split systems

01:29:55.000 --> 01:29:57.000
and the volume of sales of our company.

01:29:57.000 --> 01:29:59.000
The characteristics of the systems

01:29:59.000 --> 01:30:01.000
were presented to them.

01:30:01.000 --> 01:30:03.000
Each expert predicted the figures

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:05.000
separately from each other.

01:30:05.000 --> 01:30:07.000
Then they sent it to us.

01:30:07.000 --> 01:30:09.000
We compared all the figures

01:30:09.000 --> 01:30:11.000
and saw that there was a big difference

01:30:11.000 --> 01:30:13.000
between the predicted figures.

01:30:13.000 --> 01:30:15.000
What did we do next?

01:30:15.000 --> 01:30:17.000
We put all the figures together

01:30:17.000 --> 01:30:19.000
into a single document

01:30:19.000 --> 01:30:21.000
and sent it to each expert.

01:30:21.000 --> 01:30:23.000
What was the purpose of this?

01:30:23.000 --> 01:30:25.000
I read it and thought

01:30:25.000 --> 01:30:27.000
that I did not take into account

01:30:27.000 --> 01:30:29.000
the fact that the second expert

01:30:29.000 --> 01:30:31.000
was right and I would agree

01:30:31.000 --> 01:30:33.000
that the figures should be changed

01:30:33.000 --> 01:30:35.000
in a positive or negative way.

01:30:35.000 --> 01:30:37.000
Someone said the opposite.

01:30:37.000 --> 01:30:39.000
I do not agree with this.

01:30:39.000 --> 01:30:41.000
I am not going to change my figure.

01:30:41.000 --> 01:30:43.000
Thus, we need to make

01:30:43.000 --> 01:30:45.000
so many visits to the experts

01:30:45.000 --> 01:30:47.000
until the difference

01:30:47.000 --> 01:30:49.000
between their figures

01:30:49.000 --> 01:30:51.000
is not visible

01:30:51.000 --> 01:30:53.000
and the difference

01:30:53.000 --> 01:30:55.000
between their figures

01:30:55.000 --> 01:30:57.000
is not more than 10%.

01:30:57.000 --> 01:30:59.000
Then we can rely on this information.

01:30:59.000 --> 01:31:01.000
Thus, we got a very good result

01:31:01.000 --> 01:31:03.000
in two visits.

01:31:03.000 --> 01:31:05.000
What was surprising

01:31:05.000 --> 01:31:07.000
was that the figures of the experts

01:31:07.000 --> 01:31:09.000
matched the market's

01:31:09.000 --> 01:31:11.000
customer's assessment.

01:31:11.000 --> 01:31:13.000
We took this figure

01:31:13.000 --> 01:31:15.000
for our sales forecast.

01:31:15.000 --> 01:31:17.000
We got a very good result.

01:31:17.000 --> 01:31:19.000
I want to say that

01:31:19.000 --> 01:31:21.000
when we summed up the results

01:31:21.000 --> 01:31:23.000
after a year,

01:31:23.000 --> 01:31:25.000
we made a mistake of 5%.

01:31:25.000 --> 01:31:27.000
Our managers sold

01:31:27.000 --> 01:31:29.000
5% more.

01:31:29.000 --> 01:31:31.000
This was a very good result.

